# Ledger Entry Schema

```json
{
  "$schema": "http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#",
  "title": "LedgerEntry",
  "type": "object",
  "required": ["seq", "type", "agent", "timestamp", "payload", "hash", "prev_hash"],
  "properties": {
    "seq": {
      "type": "integer",
      "minimum": 1,
      "description": "Monotonic sequence number"
    },
    "type": {
      "type": "string",
      "enum": [
        "TASK_CREATED",
        "TASK_ASSIGNED",
        "TASK_COMPLETED",
        "TASK_REJECTED",
        "ACTION_SEALED",
        "BREACH",
        "DUPLICATE",
        "REJECTED",
        "CHECKPOINT"
      ],
      "description": "Event type"
    },
    "agent": {
      "type": "string",
      "enum": ["FORGE", "SENTINEL", "LEDGE", "OPERATOR", "SYSTEM"],
      "description": "Agent that produced this entry"
    },
    "timestamp": {
      "type": "string",
      "format": "date-time",
      "description": "ISO 8601 timestamp"
    },
    "payload": {
      "type": "object",
      "description": "Event-specific data"
    },
    "hash": {
      "type": "string",
      "pattern": "^[a-f0-9]{64}$",
      "description": "SHA-256 hash of this entry"
    },
    "prev_hash": {
      "type": "string",
      "pattern": "^[a-f0-9]{64}$",
      "description": "SHA-256 hash of previous entry (or GENESIS for first entry)"
    }
  },
  "additionalProperties": false
}
```

## Hash Chain Rules

1. First entry has `prev_hash = "0".repeat(64)` (genesis block)
2. Each subsequent entry's `prev_hash` must equal the previous entry's `hash`
3. `hash = SHA-256(seq + type + agent + timestamp + JSON.stringify(payload) + prev_hash)`
4. Any break in the chain halts all operations (F-004)

## Integrity Verification

```text
For each entry E[i] where i > 0:
  assert E[i].prev_hash == E[i-1].hash
  assert E[i].hash == compute_hash(E[i])
  assert E[i].seq == E[i-1].seq + 1
```
